    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  chronic low back pain (â‰¥ 3 months)

          -  clinical suspicion of lumbo-sacral instability

          -  functional conventional radiographs of lumbar spine

          -  pain intensity &gt; 4 / 10 on visual analogue scale

          -  age 20-60 years

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  radicular pain

          -  pain at more than two locations

          -  lumbar spine surgery

          -  scoliosis

          -  lumbar spondylolysis

          -  lumbar spondylodiscitis

          -  anatomic aberrations of lumbar spine

          -  unconsolidated spine fractures

          -  neurologic deficits

          -  spine tumor

          -  neuromuscular disease

          -  rheumatic disease

          -  severe osteoporosis

          -  radiotherapy within the last 5 years

          -  pregnancy

          -  insufficient German language skills

          -  no informed consent
      </textblock>
